<p>*The value of BBLS facilities approved includes BBLS loans which have been â€˜topped-upâ€™ â€“ that is, as announced on 2 November, BBLS borrowers who took out less than their maximum under the scheme rules (the lesser of Â£50,000 or 25% of their turnover) in their first loan application can top-up their loan up to the maximum. As of 13 December, 62,311 BBLS top-ups had been approved worth Â£0.56 billion.</p>

<p>One topped up loan will still be reported as one loan to avoid double counting the number of facilities approved. (e.g. if there were previously two facilities worth Â£40,000 each and subsequently one had been topped up to Â£50,000, this would now be reported as two facilities worth a total of Â£90,000).</p>

